Oops! You forgot to wrap Mutex in an `Arc`. The error message says the trait Send isn't implemented on Mutex, but it is on Arc<Mutex<T>>. So change your code like this:

```rust
use std::{sync::{Arc, Mutex}, thread};

fn main() {
    let data = Arc::new(Mutex::new(0));
    let mut handles = vec![];
    for _ in 0..10 {
        let handle = thread::spawn(move || {
            *data.lock().unwrap() += 1;
        });
        handles.push(handle);
    }
    for h in handles { h.join().unwrap(); }
}
```

